00:53.470 --> 00:54.936
Night terrors?

00:54.971 --> 00:56.730
I haven't had them in years.

00:56.765 --> 01:00.101
Usually it's
brought on by distress.

01:00.136 --> 01:03.438
Maybe it's my
breakup with Tara.

01:04.272 --> 01:05.947
You jump off balconies?

01:05.982 --> 01:09.110
I could where I
happen to be living.

01:09.569 --> 01:12.654
I see images of someone or

01:12.739 --> 01:16.074
something after me
and in my sleep, I run.

01:16.110 --> 01:19.412
–It's awful.
–Last week it was clowns.

01:21.623 --> 01:23.666
Denny…

01:23.833 --> 01:27.211
how would you feel
about sleeping with me?

01:27.246 --> 01:29.887
Next to me, until this passes,

01:29.922 --> 01:32.967
just to make sure I
don't leap off the 14th floor.

01:33.002 --> 01:35.004
You'll do anything
to get me into bed.

01:35.004 --> 01:38.014
Denny, night terrors, they can

01:38.097 --> 01:41.058
be potentially
life-threatening.

01:46.147 --> 01:48.030
Because we're friends,

01:48.065 --> 01:53.321
I'm gonna tell you something
that nobody else knows.

01:56.032 --> 01:57.846
I'm homophobic.

01:57.881 --> 01:59.625
I'm stunned.

01:59.660 --> 02:02.955
Look, I'd do
almost anything for you,

02:02.990 --> 02:05.583
but I cannot share my bed.

02:05.750 --> 02:08.402
Be a man. Get a girl.

02:39.582 --> 02:40.532
Ass fat!

02:40.603 --> 02:41.448
Pardon?

02:41.519 --> 02:42.843
Tori, let me.

02:42.922 --> 02:43.895
She gets upset.

02:43.973 --> 02:45.376
Okay, Tori and I
have been friends

02:45.376 --> 02:46.818
since I won't
even tell you how long,

02:46.818 --> 02:48.493
so when we decided
to have our lips done…

02:48.493 --> 02:50.285
–We had our lips done.
–We did our research.

02:50.285 --> 02:51.844
And we found the
best lip man in Boston.

02:51.844 --> 02:52.935
Reputed to be the best.

02:52.935 --> 02:54.337
–Yes, and he
doesn't use collagen

02:54.337 --> 02:55.740
He doesn't use
collagen, instead…

02:55.740 --> 02:57.454
Instead he sticks a
hollow needle into you,

02:57.454 --> 02:58.583
you know, back there,

02:58.583 --> 03:00.493
and he removes a sample
of fat from the buttocks.

03:00.493 --> 03:02.519
–Lasts longer than collagen.
–Oh, totally natural.

03:02.519 --> 03:03.883
He then injects
it into the lips,

03:03.883 --> 03:05.168
making them
youthful and lovely.

03:05.168 --> 03:06.103
Very hygienic.

03:06.181 --> 03:07.544
And it was all
good and fine until

03:07.544 --> 03:08.948
one day last
week, we got a call…

03:08.948 --> 03:10.818
We got a call from
his physician's assistant.

03:10.818 --> 03:12.493
She was present at all of the

03:12.571 --> 03:14.207
procedures, not
attractive, not happy.

03:14.207 --> 03:15.766
And she told us
that our doctor…

03:15.766 --> 03:16.701
Oh, God.

03:16.778 --> 03:18.348
… has been injecting his own

03:18.415 --> 03:19.973
ass fat into women's lips.

03:20.052 --> 03:21.142
His own…

03:21.220 --> 03:23.012
Yes. We want to
sue Dr Glouberman.

03:23.012 --> 03:23.947
For fraud.

03:24.025 --> 03:25.350
–Or malpractice.
–Or something.

03:25.350 --> 03:27.376
I have the
man's ass in my face.

03:27.454 --> 03:31.661
Did you say Dr Glouberman,
Dr Barry Glouberman?

03:31.740 --> 03:34.077
She's had work. I told you.

03:34.155 --> 03:36.376
Dr Glouberman is a
client at this firm.

03:36.454 --> 03:38.791
We structured his corporation,
among other things,

03:38.791 --> 03:41.909
so we can't represent you in
any action against him.

03:41.986 --> 03:43.311
Well, that's stupid.

03:43.389 --> 03:45.298
In fact, if you do sue

03:45.376 --> 03:47.207
him, I'll be the one he calls.

03:47.285 --> 03:49.329
I can't represent you.

03:49.414 --> 03:51.373
This whole thing is absurd.

03:51.459 --> 03:52.949
Any number of people could

03:52.949 --> 03:54.354
have run over that old man.

03:54.354 --> 03:56.781
But Jason's the one
about to go on trial.

03:56.781 --> 03:57.846
With an alibi.

03:57.931 --> 03:59.847
Who happens to be his father.

03:59.933 --> 04:01.764
Are you saying that
you don't believe me?

04:01.764 --> 04:03.296
Of course we believe you.

04:03.298 --> 04:05.640
We even believe the part
about the car being stolen.

04:05.640 --> 04:07.214
We believe it all, Ronald.

04:07.214 --> 04:09.174
That's why you pay us.

04:09.260 --> 04:11.403
We're not saying we can't win.

04:11.491 --> 04:14.483
How can you not
win? My son has an alibi.

04:14.572 --> 04:16.492
There's no physical

04:16.581 --> 04:18.457
evidence linking
him to the crime.

04:18.457 --> 04:22.296
–The car.
–Which was stolen.

04:22.386 --> 04:30.426
Jason, do you
have anything to say?

04:31.102 --> 04:32.103
I did it.

04:32.186 --> 04:33.438
Son…

04:33.521 --> 04:35.023
Dad…

04:36.691 --> 04:39.152
I ran that guy over.

04:42.946 --> 04:44.741
I did it.

04:55.543 --> 04:57.461
No, no. I paid that.

04:57.496 --> 04:58.959
On the, uh…

04:58.994 --> 05:00.423
the, uh…

05:00.923 --> 05:02.139
14th.

05:02.174 --> 05:05.094
Yeah, well, my records
clearly show that I did.

05:05.129 --> 05:06.477
Yeah, well…

05:06.512 --> 05:08.139
Yeah, well,
maybe, maybe I'm the

05:08.139 --> 05:09.557
victim of
identity theft, okay?

05:09.557 --> 05:12.893
Okay, maybe, maybe,
I am not who I am, huh?

05:12.928 --> 05:14.854
Have you thought of that?

05:19.233 --> 05:21.145
Obviously, we can't
call Jason to the stand.

05:21.145 --> 05:22.611
We'd be suborning perjury.

05:22.611 --> 05:25.322
I talked to the kid.
He won't admit it again.

05:25.357 --> 05:28.075
Denny, we cannot knowingly put

05:28.159 --> 05:30.786
a client on the stand to lie.

05:30.828 --> 05:32.210
Because?

05:32.246 --> 05:33.789
Fortunately, we
may not have to.

05:33.789 --> 05:36.208
Our only eyewitness
suffers from Alzheimer's.

05:36.208 --> 05:38.287
The state may well not
be able to make their case.

05:38.287 --> 05:40.080
What about the other
witness who saw the car?

05:40.080 --> 05:41.136
Which was stolen.

05:41.171 --> 05:42.923
Oh, right. I keep forgetting.

05:42.958 --> 05:44.675
I'd like you to canvass the

05:44.758 --> 05:46.218
neighborhood one last time,

05:46.218 --> 05:48.470
see if anybody
else saw anything.

05:48.554 --> 05:49.930
In the meantime, Paul, maybe

05:49.930 --> 05:51.265
you could
visit our eyewitness,

05:51.265 --> 05:53.976
see what we're dealing with.

05:54.059 --> 05:57.020
You're the one who will
be crossing her, Shirley.

05:57.104 --> 05:59.815
Those assisted
living places…

05:59.898 --> 06:01.358
I'm sorry, I know

06:01.442 --> 06:03.110
heebie-jeebies
isn't a legal term but…

06:03.110 --> 06:04.611
It needs to be you,

06:04.695 --> 06:06.113
Shirley. You're
trying this case.

06:06.113 --> 06:09.658
You need to
interview this woman.

06:14.288 --> 06:15.546
This is ridiculous.

06:15.581 --> 06:16.957
And the women claim that it's

06:16.957 --> 06:18.160
your old physician's assistant

06:18.160 --> 06:19.873
that's the whistle-blower.

06:19.908 --> 06:21.551
Helen? I had to fire her.

06:21.586 --> 06:23.297
The woman broke a needle three

06:23.297 --> 06:24.833
times in three
different patients.

06:24.833 --> 06:26.341
She was a
danger to my clients.

06:26.341 --> 06:27.361
Barry, calm down.

06:27.425 --> 06:29.106
Yeah, it was either fire her

06:29.136 --> 06:30.762
or send my malpractice

06:30.846 --> 06:32.514
insurance
screaming through the roof.

06:32.514 --> 06:35.517
So then she turns
around and sues me.

06:35.600 --> 06:38.103
Fired for
wrongful termination.

06:38.186 --> 06:39.686
And we took care of that.

06:39.688 --> 06:43.441
This kind of
allegation alone, though…

06:43.525 --> 06:45.694
What am I gonna do?

06:45.777 --> 06:47.279
We need to meet
with this woman,

06:47.279 --> 06:49.447
your ex-nurse,
get her to recant.

06:49.531 --> 06:51.074
It's the best way to head

06:51.157 --> 06:52.659
this lawsuit off at the pass.

06:52.659 --> 06:55.287
She's a vicious,
spiteful, treacherous pig.

06:55.370 --> 06:56.705
That's what she is.

06:56.788 --> 06:58.748
I'm not gonna lead with that.

06:58.832 --> 07:00.667
Do I need to meet with her

07:00.750 --> 07:02.460
alone, or can you be civil?

07:04.796 --> 07:07.292
Oh, are you illiterate
or you just can't read?

07:07.292 --> 07:08.306
You know…

07:08.341 --> 07:11.594
No, “final notice” means that
it's the final notice.

07:11.629 --> 07:13.923
Otherwise it would
say, “final shutoff.”

07:13.923 --> 07:15.014
Suppose I was in my

07:15.014 --> 07:16.558
apartment hooked
up to a respirator.

07:16.558 --> 07:18.268
I would be dead
right now, okay?

07:18.268 --> 07:19.853
You would be
talking to a dead person.

07:19.853 --> 07:21.604
Melissa?

07:27.861 --> 07:30.905
Would you excuse us, please?

07:36.035 --> 07:38.288
From what I
gather, you seem to be

07:38.371 --> 07:40.706
having some
financial difficulties.

07:40.741 --> 07:43.042
Oh, no, no, no.
I'm just a, uh…

07:43.077 --> 07:44.384
a shopper.

07:44.419 --> 07:45.962
You know, there's
a certain power to

07:45.962 --> 07:47.505
being able to buy
anything you want,

07:47.505 --> 07:49.340
and I don't know, have you

07:49.424 --> 07:51.217
been to the
new pottery barrel?

07:51.217 --> 07:52.635
–No.
–No.

07:52.718 --> 07:55.763
If you get their
catalog, turn to page 37.

07:55.847 --> 07:57.306
That's my bedroom.

07:57.390 --> 08:01.435
Would you like to earn
some extra money, Melissa?

08:01.519 --> 08:05.314
Uh, how?

08:06.524 --> 08:10.069
I have a condition.

08:10.903 --> 08:13.913
It's called night terrors.

08:13.948 --> 08:21.080
During the deepest
levels of non-REM sleep,

08:21.115 --> 08:24.834
I hear voices,
terrifying voices,

08:24.869 --> 08:27.218
and sometimes I run.

08:27.253 --> 08:32.299
Since I'm sound
asleep when I'm running,

08:32.333 --> 08:37.346
this puts me in
significant physical danger.

08:38.806 --> 08:43.143
I need somebody
to guard me at night.

08:43.178 --> 08:46.355
When you say “guard”…

08:46.522 --> 08:50.504
I need you to lie
in the bed with me.

08:50.540 --> 08:54.488
Should I get up to
run outside, stop me.

08:57.199 --> 08:59.639
How stupid do you think I am?

08:59.674 --> 09:02.079
So you'll think about it?

09:15.843 --> 09:19.680
Lydia, this is
Shirley Schmidt.

09:19.715 --> 09:22.396
–Hello, Lydia.
–Hello.

09:22.432 --> 09:24.851
–Who is she, Toque?
–Shirley Schmidt.

09:24.893 --> 09:26.395
She was going to talk to you

09:26.395 --> 09:27.854
about Albert
being hit by the car.

09:27.854 --> 09:30.399
Yes, I know.

09:30.482 --> 09:32.234
Where's my apple juice?

09:32.317 --> 09:34.403
I'm getting it now.

09:36.697 --> 09:40.158
–Your violets are lovely.
–Ceramic pots.

09:40.193 --> 09:43.745
Never terra-cotta. They
collect salt.

09:43.780 --> 09:45.831
But you're not here for that.

09:45.866 --> 09:48.166
No, I'm afraid I'm not.

09:51.586 --> 09:54.005
Here's a little
one all dressed up.

09:54.040 --> 09:56.108
My granddaughter.

09:56.142 --> 09:58.176
Oh, she's adorable.

09:59.302 --> 10:01.116
What's her name?

10:01.151 --> 10:02.896
You're testing me.

10:02.931 --> 10:06.267
–I'm afraid I am.
–Her name is Julie.

10:06.302 --> 10:09.688
She's dressed as Groucho Marx

10:09.771 --> 10:13.066
from my
favorite movie of 1939,

10:13.108 --> 10:15.617
“At the circus.”

10:15.652 --> 10:19.656
And that boy
committed the crime.

10:21.533 --> 10:24.577
People think I
don't remember things,

10:24.612 --> 10:26.871
and a lot of things I

10:26.955 --> 10:29.207
don't, like
names and so forth,

10:29.242 --> 10:33.294
but traumatic events?

10:33.503 --> 10:35.505
I'll never
forget what happened

10:35.588 --> 10:37.548
outside that
window that night.

10:37.583 --> 10:39.390
It was horrible.

10:39.425 --> 10:42.887
I'm sorry. It must
have been awful for you.

10:44.263 --> 10:46.272
Toque?

10:46.307 --> 10:48.066
This is orange juice.

10:48.101 --> 10:50.207
Oh, they were
out of apple, honey.

10:50.242 --> 10:52.403
But it's always
apple for lunch.

10:52.438 --> 10:54.565
It's okay,
Lydia. Orange is okay.

10:54.600 --> 10:55.948
No, it's not!

10:55.983 --> 10:59.362
Orange is for
breakfast. Apple's for lunch.

10:59.397 --> 11:02.830
It's always apple! Always!

11:02.864 --> 11:04.784
–Can I help?
–Here, let me help.

11:04.784 --> 11:06.946
There's nothing to
do but calm her down.

11:06.946 --> 11:08.663
It's okay, honey. It's okay.

11:08.698 --> 11:10.748
It's okay. It's okay.

11:18.547 --> 11:21.050
I was out walking my dog, when

11:21.133 --> 11:23.552
suddenly I
heard this screech…

11:23.587 --> 11:26.472
and, uh, then a thump.

11:26.507 --> 11:27.688
I turned around.

11:27.723 --> 11:30.274
I saw a white sedan speed off,

11:30.309 --> 11:33.069
uh, with a body at
the side of the road.

11:33.104 --> 11:36.164
–Were you able to get a license plate number?
–Yes.

11:36.183 --> 11:39.658
ZXL3R. Massachusetts plates.

11:39.693 --> 11:42.106
The record will
reflect the parties stipulate

11:42.106 --> 11:43.906
that the license is registered

11:43.989 --> 11:45.741
to the
defendant Jason Matheny.

11:45.741 --> 11:48.077
Thank you, Mr Nasland.

11:49.536 --> 11:51.420
Don't go rough.

11:51.455 --> 11:54.249
He just lost his
grandfather, for God's sakes.

11:54.284 --> 11:56.908
That wasn't his
grandfather who died, Denny.

11:56.908 --> 11:59.498
He's just a witness
who was walking his dog.

11:59.498 --> 12:01.632
Whatever.

12:03.092 --> 12:06.970
Sir, were you able to
see who was driving the car?

12:07.004 --> 12:08.729
–No.
–Thank you.

12:08.764 --> 12:11.009
For the record, the
parties stipulate the car was

12:11.009 --> 12:14.645
reported stolen the
night of the accident.

12:15.354 --> 12:17.773
Too rough?

12:43.840 --> 12:45.425
Standard service agreement

12:45.509 --> 12:47.191
contract, mostly boilerplate.

12:47.191 --> 12:48.887
The language
of what I will and

12:48.887 --> 12:50.555
will not do is quite specific,

12:50.555 --> 12:53.642
so there won't be
any Clintonian mishaps.

12:53.677 --> 12:56.985
“Is” means is.

12:57.020 --> 13:00.773
“No touching, no
cuddling, no sex.”

13:00.809 --> 13:02.549
You've taken out all the fun.

13:02.567 --> 13:03.652
These are my terms.

13:03.652 --> 13:05.543
For that, I will
sleep in your bed

13:05.543 --> 13:07.399
and will make
sure you don't wig out,

13:07.399 --> 13:08.955
and that's it.

13:08.990 --> 13:13.495
I'm not sure the term
“wig out” has legal teeth.

13:13.530 --> 13:16.206
But it is extremely Xeroxable

13:16.289 --> 13:18.917
for all the
partners' windshields.

13:20.668 --> 13:22.427
Thank you, Melissa.

13:22.462 --> 13:27.050
I give you my word I'll honor
all your terms and…

13:27.085 --> 13:29.093
thank you.

13:31.679 --> 13:34.015
I'll see you at 10 o'clock.

13:38.394 --> 13:40.160
Wait a second.
You're denying this?

13:40.160 --> 13:42.127
–Of course I'm denying it.
–Barry…

13:42.127 --> 13:44.060
–It never happened.
–I was there!

13:44.060 --> 13:46.069
Hold on. Barry.

13:46.361 --> 13:47.814
When you say you were there…

13:47.814 --> 13:49.280
I helped him remove his own

13:49.280 --> 13:50.740
fat cells from his buttocks.

13:50.740 --> 13:52.700
–To use on myself.
–Barry…

13:52.784 --> 13:54.077
That's what you said, Barry.

13:54.077 --> 13:55.912
Look, I removed the cells, I

13:55.995 --> 13:57.789
harvested the fat,
and I marked the vials.

13:57.789 --> 13:59.949
And I saw him go
to the vials to use

13:59.957 --> 14:02.043
that fat to
inject into other women.

14:02.043 --> 14:04.170
Then why didn't you say
something if you thought…

14:04.170 --> 14:05.379
Because I first thought it

14:05.379 --> 14:06.714
was with the
patients' consent,

14:06.714 --> 14:09.050
And then I asked a few.
–Asked them what?

14:09.050 --> 14:10.218
Where the harvested fat for

14:10.218 --> 14:11.385
their procedures came from.

14:11.385 --> 14:12.637
They said their own buttocks.

14:12.637 --> 14:13.721
Which is the truth.

14:13.721 --> 14:14.805
Barry… Oh, please!

14:14.889 --> 14:17.391
You're just trying to ruin me.

14:17.475 --> 14:18.476
Barry.

14:18.559 --> 14:21.062
Ms Gershen,
obviously this kind of charge,

14:21.062 --> 14:22.313
when it goes to a person's

14:22.313 --> 14:23.522
profession, is libel per se.

14:23.522 --> 14:27.193
We wouldn't even have
to show actual damages.

14:27.276 --> 14:29.737
I'm no lawyer,
but on the TV shows,

14:29.820 --> 14:32.156
they say truth is
a defense to libel.

14:32.239 --> 14:33.324
I see.

14:33.407 --> 14:35.534
And are you prepared to prove

14:35.618 --> 14:37.703
the truth of
these allegations?

14:37.787 --> 14:39.413
Sure.

14:39.497 --> 14:41.457
May I ask how?

14:41.540 --> 14:43.640
Do DNA on him.
Do it on their lips.

14:43.709 --> 14:45.252
You'll see a match.

14:45.336 --> 14:47.838
Won't she, Barry?

14:48.631 --> 14:50.973
I'm not giving
any DNA samples.

14:51.008 --> 14:55.554
That's, um,
unconstitutional, right?

14:58.891 --> 15:00.970
You met with the
woman, Shirley. Certainly…

15:00.970 --> 15:02.680
I don't want to do
it. It's that simple.

15:02.680 --> 15:04.653
No, it is not that simple.

15:04.688 --> 15:06.649
We have an
obligation as attorneys…

15:06.649 --> 15:09.818
Oh, spare me the speech,
Paul, would you please?

15:09.853 --> 15:12.073
Well, evidently,
you need the speech.

15:12.106 --> 15:13.546
Like it or not, this job

15:13.614 --> 15:15.636
gets dirty from time to time.

15:15.671 --> 15:17.659
What the hell
is going on here?

15:17.743 --> 15:18.786
It's just..

15:20.287 --> 15:23.165
preying on somebody
with Alzheimer's when…

15:23.200 --> 15:26.043
obviously I'm a
little sensitive given…

15:26.078 --> 15:28.135
Given what?

15:28.170 --> 15:30.214
I say a if a woman's
brain has turned to oatmeal,

15:30.214 --> 15:32.466
let's throw in some raisins

15:32.549 --> 15:34.635
and have her for breakfast.

15:34.718 --> 15:36.386
What, you think you have to

15:36.470 --> 15:38.096
handle me with
kid gloves, Shirley?

15:38.096 --> 15:40.057
This case has nothing
to do with you, Denny.

15:40.057 --> 15:42.351
Don't lie to me.

15:42.434 --> 15:45.937
Would you excuse
us for a second, Paul?

15:50.692 --> 15:52.152
I know how terrified you are.

15:52.152 --> 15:54.613
–I'm afraid of nothing.
–Denny…

15:54.654 --> 15:56.990
whether or not
you have some mild

15:57.073 --> 15:59.402
