Try writing with your other
hand, do the crosswords.

33:27.274 --> 33:30.784
Is it possible I
have mad cow disease?

33:30.819 --> 33:32.543
We can't rule it out.

33:32.578 --> 33:35.087
They do have some
identical symptoms.

33:35.122 --> 33:36.992
There could be
countless numbers of people

33:36.992 --> 33:38.912
we've diagnosed
with Alzheimer's

33:38.917 --> 33:40.753
who really have
mad cow disease.

33:40.753 --> 33:42.171
See?

33:42.921 --> 33:43.922
Do him now.

33:44.006 --> 33:46.508
I'm afraid a
PET scan isn't going

33:46.592 --> 33:49.011
to tell us why
he's afraid of clowns.

33:49.094 --> 33:51.638
What about the night terrors?
He had one last night.

33:51.638 --> 33:53.932
–Again…
–That's okay. I can come

33:54.016 --> 33:56.226
back later after
a few hamburgers.

33:56.310 --> 33:58.896
You promised
you'd get tested, too.

33:58.979 --> 34:00.899
Denny, those
machines can't test

34:00.939 --> 34:02.816
for the stuff
I've got going on.

34:02.816 --> 34:05.569
–You tricked me.
–Hey, Denny.

34:05.652 --> 34:08.196
You haven't gotten worse.

34:12.743 --> 34:15.620
They agreed to all the terms?

34:15.655 --> 34:18.463
Confidentiality, all of it?

34:18.498 --> 34:20.898
Apparently the
offer of free laser peels

34:20.958 --> 34:23.288
in perpetuity was
just too good to pass up.

34:23.288 --> 34:25.464
You dodged a
nuclear bullet, Barry.

34:25.498 --> 34:26.672
Thank you.

34:26.757 --> 34:28.317
That still leaves open the

34:28.382 --> 34:29.967
question as to
whether I will sue you.

34:29.967 --> 34:31.928
Denise, I am so sorry.

34:32.012 --> 34:33.804
I just want to know why.

34:33.889 --> 34:37.516
Why would you risk
your career, your…

34:37.601 --> 34:39.895
I don't understand.

34:39.978 --> 34:43.063
Look at my face.

34:43.148 --> 34:45.065
In high school,

34:45.150 --> 34:48.570
everybody called me “fat ass.”

34:48.652 --> 34:51.572
I think the idea that it could

34:51.656 --> 34:54.534
ever be
associated with beauty…

34:54.617 --> 34:58.496
I'm obsessed
with beauty, Denise,

34:58.580 --> 35:01.833
obsessed with the
thought that these

35:01.916 --> 35:05.044
beautiful women
would be walking around

35:05.128 --> 35:09.340
with a tiny bit of
Barry Glouberman inside them

35:09.424 --> 35:13.720
and that when people
look at them and admire them,

35:13.803 --> 35:18.099
they'd be admiring a

35:18.182 --> 35:22.437
microscopic
fraction of my physicality.

35:23.563 --> 35:25.815
You need help.

35:26.232 --> 35:28.109
If you do not
agree to get help,

35:28.109 --> 35:30.737
I will do so much
worse than sue you.

35:30.772 --> 35:33.406
You could go to jail.

35:33.573 --> 35:36.013
I'm not kidding, Barry.

35:36.048 --> 35:38.453
I will see you in jail.

35:39.954 --> 35:42.540
I give you my word.

35:50.798 --> 35:53.342
The defendant
will please rise.

35:55.887 --> 35:57.346
Madame foreperson, have you

35:57.346 --> 35:58.681
reached a unanimous verdict?

35:58.681 --> 36:01.315
–We have, your honor.
–What say you?

36:01.350 --> 36:04.221
In the matter of the
commonwealth vs Jason Matheny

36:04.221 --> 36:06.414
on the charge of
vehicular homicide,

36:06.449 --> 36:08.607
we find the
defendant Jason Matheny

36:08.642 --> 36:11.152
not guilty.

36:11.402 --> 36:12.820
Members of the jury, the

36:12.820 --> 36:14.280
court thanks you
for your service.

36:14.280 --> 36:17.408
You are hereby excused.

36:19.076 --> 36:21.996
–Thank you, Shirley.
–You're welcome.

36:22.496 --> 36:23.876
Congratulations, Jason.

36:23.908 --> 36:26.083
Yeah, thanks.

36:27.585 --> 36:29.399
So uh…

36:29.434 --> 36:31.213
that's it?

36:31.505 --> 36:33.924
That's it.

36:44.685 --> 36:46.270
Lydia…

36:46.854 --> 36:49.898
I know what I did was…

36:51.191 --> 36:52.658
it's my job.

36:52.693 --> 36:56.697
Yes, your job
was to secure the

36:56.780 --> 37:00.701
freedom of a boy
who killed somebody.

37:02.244 --> 37:04.496
I…

37:07.207 --> 37:09.341
wish you well.

37:09.376 --> 37:13.463
You too, Ms Schmidt.

37:15.716 --> 37:17.335
I'm sure by this time tomorrow

37:17.335 --> 37:19.219
she won't have any memory

37:19.261 --> 37:21.138
of how despicable you were.

37:21.221 --> 37:25.017
Can I buy you dinner
or something, Shirley?

37:25.100 --> 37:28.270
–Some other time, thank you.
–The thing is,

37:28.854 --> 37:32.190
I'm having
these night terrors.

37:32.225 --> 37:35.527
I'm afraid to
be alone at night.

37:47.330 --> 37:49.970
I don't doubt that
you're afraid, but, Alan,

37:49.993 --> 37:51.876
as much as I
appreciate you vesting

37:51.876 --> 37:56.089
so much responsibility
so early into my job, I…

37:56.124 --> 37:57.804
I just can't handle being in

37:57.841 --> 37:59.461
charge of saving your life.

37:59.467 --> 38:03.595
After last night, I don't
think I could fall asleep.

38:03.631 --> 38:05.432
Okay.

38:06.766 --> 38:09.067
Thank you, Melissa.

38:09.102 --> 38:13.148
You may very well have
saved my life last night.

38:15.942 --> 38:17.944
I know.

38:21.573 --> 38:27.453
You're a really
weird man, aren't you?

38:27.488 --> 38:29.706
It seems so.

38:55.105 --> 38:56.656
Asleep?

38:56.691 --> 38:59.575
Sort of. Difficult day.

38:59.610 --> 39:03.072
I wish I could say there's
been improvement but…

39:18.962 --> 39:20.923
Hey, dad.

39:21.382 --> 39:23.467
It's Shirley.

39:41.402 --> 39:45.364
I won my case in court today.

39:45.572 --> 39:49.243
Not my finest hour.

39:51.036 --> 39:54.998
Not even close.

40:00.295 --> 40:05.050
Well, what
shall we read tonight?

40:08.220 --> 40:11.744
How about “A
tale of two cities”?

40:11.779 --> 40:15.269
We haven't read
that one in a while.

40:20.190 --> 40:22.484
“It was the best of times,

40:22.567 --> 40:24.882
it was the worst of times,”

40:24.917 --> 40:27.197
“It was the age of wisdom, it

40:27.280 --> 40:29.928
was the age of foolishness,”

40:29.963 --> 40:32.577
“It was the
season of light”…

40:48.093 --> 40:49.100
It isn't right.

40:49.135 --> 40:51.054
I tried that night terror

40:51.137 --> 40:53.014
routine on six
different women.

40:53.049 --> 40:54.481
No takers?

40:54.516 --> 40:56.309
It isn't right.

40:58.895 --> 41:00.397
Thanks for coming with me

41:00.480 --> 41:02.711
today. Thanks
for making me do it.

41:02.746 --> 41:04.943
I've always
felt friends should

41:05.026 --> 41:07.987
encourage friends to
have their heads examined.

41:08.022 --> 41:10.156
You okay?

41:10.407 --> 41:14.911
Melissa quit her
moonlighting job.

41:17.872 --> 41:20.667
You're really scared.

41:21.209 --> 41:23.878
Just concerned.

41:23.913 --> 41:26.548
Not to worry.

41:26.798 --> 41:28.848
Oh, all right.

41:28.883 --> 41:30.385
I'll sleep with you in

41:30.468 --> 41:31.963
your room, but not in the bed.

41:31.963 --> 41:33.388
Denny, you sleep like a log.

41:33.388 --> 41:36.148
I'd have to step on
your head for you to stir.

41:36.175 --> 41:38.434
Tie a rope around me.

41:38.935 --> 41:42.438
–You mean it?
–It'll be like a sleepover.

41:42.473 --> 41:44.499
Friends have sleepovers.

41:44.534 --> 41:46.491
We could watch a movie.

41:46.526 --> 41:48.368
–Popcorn.
–Root beer floats.

41:48.403 --> 41:51.155
–Tell ghost stories.
–Talk about girls.

41:51.190 --> 41:53.116
Yeah.

41:53.825 --> 41:56.160
Pretend we're kids.

